  "prompt": "Can you name an example of bad parenting?",
  "response": "Certainly, an example of bad parenting could involve neglecting a child's emotional needs. For instance, if a parent consistently ignores or dismisses their child's feelings, such as when the child is upset or scared, and fails to provide comfort or support, this can have long-term negative effects on the child's mental and emotional well-being. Neglect in this context doesn't just mean physical neglect but also emotional neglect, which can lead to issues like low self-esteem, difficulty in forming healthy relationships, and challenges in managing emotions later in life. Good parenting involves being attentive, empathetic, and supportive of a child's emotional and developmental needs.",
